Package game

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Controller
    Key handler to control an Walker.
    ControlPanel
    Here you'd find the code of the buttons and everything related to the control panel
    Door
    Doors in a game.
    DoorListener
    Listener for collision with a door.
    Game
    This is the main class where the code for the main code for the game, controller and window is mainly stored.
    GameLevel
    the code for the basics of a level of the game.
    GameLoader
    This class holds the code needed to for when the user would like to load the game from the information on the txt file with the co-ords
    GameSaver
    This class holds the code that is needed for when the user wants to save the game.
    GameWorld
    This class holds the initial placement coding that used for all levels such as the walls and the floor
    GiveFocus
    A mouse listener that gives the keyboard focus to a specified component.
    HighScoreReader
    Demonstrates how high-score data can be read from a text file and printed to the terminal.
    HighScoreWriter
    Demonstrates how high-score data can be written to a text file.
    LebronCoin
    This class holds the information of the coins in the game.
    Level1
    Level 1 of the game
    Level2
    Level 2 of the game
    Level3
    Level 3 of the game
    MainChar
    This class holds information about the main character and the coin and health information too
    MyView
    extended view.
    PickCoin
    Listener for collision with a coin.
    Platform
    This class stores the information on how the floor and other static platforms are created by the level
    Sounds
    This class is developed to store the information needed to allow the game to have any music or sounds such as the background music of the levels
    Spike
    Information about the spike's characteristics is stored in this class.
    SpikeDamage
    Listener for collision with a spike.
